<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:01AM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONCERNS TODAY FOR MASSACHUSETTS, RHODE
ISLAND AND CONNECTICUT...
Significant drought conditions across Massachusetts, Rhode Island,
and Connecticut will result in elevated fire weather concerns for
today and will continue until the region receives wetting rains.
Relative humidity values will drop to between 25 and 40 percent
across portions of the interior this afternoon with southwest
winds winds 5 and 10 mph with gusts to 15 mph.
Any fire that ignites can easily and rapidly spread in these
conditions.</description>
